  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You may create content for the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://www.apple.com/swift/playgrounds/",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "app by writing playground books. Like traditional books, playground books are made",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "up of chapters and pages. Unlike traditional books, they include executable Swift",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "code that displays the results live, right on the page.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The pages of a playground book can include features that you use to teach a lesson",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or to encourage code experimentation. The basic building blocks you use are:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Prose that introduces the material on the page.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blocks and modules of Swift code that learners can edit and expand upon.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "The always-on live view that you use to show visualizations of running the page’s",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "code.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following screenshot of a page from Learn to Code 1 shows a lesson on the left",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and an interactive live view on the right.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "swift-playgrounds-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can further enrich a playground book and tailor it to your audience by adding",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "cutscenes, glossaries, hints, and assessments. When you’re done writing a playground",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "book, you can distribute it locally in a classroom or workshop environment, or publish",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "it online as a subscription.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
